  "statement": {
    "title": "CPU native_layer_norm decomposition returns wrong dtype under fake tensor dispatch",
    "body": "When `torch.ops.aten.native_layer_norm.default` is invoked under `FakeTensorMode` with the Python dispatcher enabled, the decomposition path in `torch/_refs/__init__.py` misses the CPU-specific low-precision upcast/return-dtype handling that eager CPU native_layer_norm performs. Result: `native_layer_norm` output dtype under fake tensor dispatch diverges from the real eager CPU output dtype for bf16 inputs.\n\nFix (~5 lines in `torch/_refs/__init__.py`): register a dedicated fake impl for `aten.native_layer_norm.default` that dispatches through the real `native_layer_norm` decomposition so the CPU-specific dtype semantics are preserved.",
    "labels": [
      "module: nn",
      "module: decomposition",
      "module: fake tensor",
      "topic: numerical"
    ]
  },
